1
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:06,040
这城市正在自我毁灭 兄弟 所以我不愿参与
This city is eating itself, man. That's why I don't get involved.

2
00:00:06,200 --> 00:00:08,080
- 我们达成交易了吗? - 成交
- Do we have a deal? - Whatever you need.

3
00:00:08,240 --> 00:00:09,640
你的红毛搭档呢? 
And your ang mo partner?  

4
00:00:09,641 --> 00:00:11,040
这是我们之间的交易
Let's just keep this between us.

5
00:00:11,160 --> 00:00:13,040
那是詹姆斯・林没错
Well, that's James Lim, right.

6
00:00:13,160 --> 00:00:14,720
他是个积极进取的生意人
He's a businessman on his way up,

7
00:00:14,880 --> 00:00:17,560
他哥哥是林杰志 工会主要领袖
and his brother is Lim Chee Kit, the senior union leader.

8
00:00:17,720 --> 00:00:20,360
我想和你一起看电影 能更了解你
I'd love to see a film with you, get to know you better.

9
00:00:20,520 --> 00:00:22,640
为什么 你想给我立档案吗?
Why, so you can open a file on me?

10
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:25,560
听着 东南亚就像一个大型血腥跷跷板...
Listen, South-East Asia is like one big, bloody seesaw...

11
00:00:25,720 --> 00:00:28,880
一边是美国中情局 另一边是英国军情六处
you have the CIA on one side, you've got MI6 on the other.

12
00:00:29,040 --> 00:00:31,640
之前中情局特工先生来找过你
Mr CIA Agent was looking for you earlier.

13
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:34,040
- 忘记他吧 苏 - 你说话像我爸似的
- Forget him, Su. - You sound like my father.

14
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:36,520
你觉得他与众不同吗? 他不是
Why do you think he's different? He's not.

15
00:00:36,680 --> 00:00:40,000
我想了想我说过的话 和相爱的人一起
I thought about what I said about being with people you love,

16
00:00:40,120 --> 00:00:41,880
创造自己的生活
about making your own life.

17
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,360
我要离开弗兰克
I'm leaving Frank.

18
00:00:54,040 --> 00:00:56,411
如果我没被录取怎么办? 
What if I don't get in? 

19
00:00:56,412 --> 00:00:57,400
你没问题的
You will.

20
00:00:57,560 --> 00:00:58,880
但我没接到任何消息  
But I haven't heard anything.  

21
00:00:58,881 --> 00:01:00,320
别担心 没问题的 相信我
Don't worry. You will, trust me.

22
00:01:00,480 --> 00:01:03,640
你会去纽约或华盛顿上学
You're going to go to school in New York or DC.

23
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:05,560
我会被调回兰利
I'm going to get posted back to Langley,

24
00:01:05,720 --> 00:01:07,720
然后我可以带着你去看球赛
then I can take you to a ball game.

25
00:01:07,880 --> 00:01:11,560
- 球赛? - 对 棒球 世上最棒的运动
- A ball game? - Yeah. Baseball. It's the greatest game in the world.

26
00:01:11,720 --> 00:01:13,950
我能带你去谢亚球场看纽约大都会的比赛 
I could take you to Shea Stadium to go and see the Mets. 

27
00:01:13,951 --> 00:01:14,800
那是我最爱的球队
That's my team.

28
00:01:14,960 --> 00:01:18,320
他们去年输了差不多109场比赛
You know that last year they lost, like, 109 games.

29
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:21,600
- 太糟糕了吧 - 是啊 他们很差劲
- That's terrible. - It is. They were awful.

30
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:25,560
我肯定这会违背城市的法令 但...
I'm sure it's against a dozen city ordinances, but...

31
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:35,080
- 康拉德 - 怎么了?
- Conrad. - What is it?

32
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:41,760
在这等我一下
Just wait here for a minute.

33
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:46,200
你们在加班吗?
You guys working late?

34
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:51,280
老板想让我们把场地准备好 迎接早上的船员
Work site. Boss needs us to get it ready for the morning crew.

35
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:53,480
趴下 趴下!
Down, down!

36
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:01,520
你没事吧?
You OK?

37
00:02:03,440 --> 00:02:05,480
在这等着警察来
Stay here. Wait for the police.

38
00:03:46,480 --> 00:03:51,480
石龙岗之路 第一季第07集

39
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:56,480
窗帘
Mm, curtains.

40
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:03,480
窗帘怎么了?
Curtains?

41
00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:07,840
我喜欢这里的窗帘 但要有点颜色才好
Yeah. I like it here, but it needs some colour.

42
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:13,425
来点自来水也许会好些 
Some running water would help too. 

43
00:04:13,426 --> 00:04:14,640
很快就会有了
All in good time.

44
00:04:19,640 --> 00:04:22,200
我们必须要这样吗?
Do we have to?

45
00:04:29,840 --> 00:04:31,320
是的
Yes.

46
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:36,800
那弗兰克怎么办?
But what about Frank?

47
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:39,960
他这周末才回来
Well, he's not back till the weekend.

48
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,760
只有四天了
That's only four days.

49
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:47,360
我得亲口告诉他 这是他应得的
He needs to hear it from me. He deserves that.

50
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:52,360
你确定吗?
Are you sure?

51
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:54,840
确定
Yes.

52
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:58,360
这就是我想要的 山姆
This is what I want, Sam.

53
00:04:59,520 --> 00:05:01,160
这一切都是我想要的
It's all I want.

54
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:07,160
这是你想要的吗?
Is it what you want?

55
00:05:09,440 --> 00:05:10,920
是的
Yeah.

56
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:19,360
你明天晚上有空吗 卡拉汉先生?
Are you free tomorrow night, Mr Callaghan?

57
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:50,520
康拉德没事吧?
Is Conrad alright?

58
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:53,560
- 你确定吗? - 只是有些割伤和瘀伤
- Are you sure? - Apart from some cuts and bruises.

59
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:55,160
大伙 看到这个了吗?
Guys, seen this?

60
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:57,240
时事日报的头条
Front page of The Chronicle.

61
00:05:57,360 --> 00:05:59,480
目击证人... 陈苏玲小姐
'Eyewitness... Miss Ch'en Su Ling.'

62
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:02,960
这下可瞒不了你父母了
Just what your parents don't need to know.

63
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:06,680
等等 他们为什么指责林杰志教授?
Hang on, why are they blaming Professor Lim Chee Kit?

64
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:10,200
似乎爆炸案的幕后操手是工会
Seems like the union is behind the bombing.

65
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:12,160
但我认识林教授 这绝对不可能
But I know Professor Lim. That's impossible.

66
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:13,840
他只主张非暴力
He advocates nonviolence only.

67
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:15,360
是啊 非暴力炸弹
Yeah, nonviolent bombs.

68
00:06:15,520 --> 00:06:19,160
他们炸毁了一个纹章 没人死亡
They blew up a coat of arms. Nobody died.

69
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:21,960
他们可能想说 看吧 独立就是个笑话
They might be trying to say, look, independence is a joke

70
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:23,440
我们还是在英国人的控制之下
and we're still under British control.

71
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:25,080
他们炸毁了一栋楼!
They blew up a building!

72
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:27,400
郑夫人
Mrs Cheng.

73
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:30,400
林先生 您怎么会下榻此地?
Mr Lim. To what do we owe the pleasure?

74
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:41,460
我哥哥和昨晚的爆炸案一点关系都没有
My brother had nothing to do with last night's bombing.

75
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:43,440
警察可不这么想
That's not what the cops think.

76
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:47,640
但是即使他们找到他 也不会逮捕他
But if they find him, they're not going to arrest him.

77
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:51,200
他们会杀了他 杀一儆百
They will make an example of Chee Kit, and they will kill him.

78
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:53,240
他们为何要怎么做?
Why would they do that?

79
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:56,400
你目击了昨晚的事
You saw what happened last night.

80
00:06:56,560 --> 00:07:01,240
那个男人 没有武器 他们还是打死了他
The man, he was unarmed, and still they shot him.

81
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:03,240
特务处和政府觉得
Well, Special Branch and the government

82
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,760
齐基特是政治威胁
see Chee Kit as a political threat.

83
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:07,400
我们能为你做什么?
What can we do for you?

84
00:07:07,520 --> 00:07:09,240
我想带齐基特去海外
I want to take Chee Kit offshore.

85
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:11,040
国内安全法规定
Internal Security Act.

86
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:13,400
要是警察抓到我们带危险分子离开岛内...
The cops catch us taking a subversive off the island...

87
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:15,360
..那就要去樟宜坐牢了
..it's a long holiday in Changi.

88
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:18,320
我不是让你带他走 只是找到他就好
I'm not asking you to take him, just find him.

89
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:20,920
等风头过了 我会自己安排船
And when it's safe, I'll arrange a boat myself.

90
00:07:21,080 --> 00:07:23,560
你有很多关系网 为什么你不自己找?
You're well connected. Why can't you find him?

91
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:30,880
我想他不会想见我 但...
I don't think he would want me to, but...

92
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,480
..毕竟他是我哥哥
..he's my brother.

93
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:40,600
为什么詹姆斯・林想让他哥哥离开岛内?
Why would James Lim want to get his brother off the island?

94
00:07:40,720 --> 00:07:43,400
齐基特很有社会正义感...
Chee Kit is Mr Social Justice...

95
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:45,440
是为马来西亚着想的马来西亚人
Malaysians for Malaysia and all that.

96
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:47,360
詹姆士不介意红毛吗?
And James doesn't mind the ang mo?

97
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:49,240
只要他能从我们这获利
As long as he can make money off us.

98
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:54,120
詹姆士有野心 政治野心
The word is, James has ambitions, political ambitions.

99
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:57,760
或许这就是他希望他哥哥离开的原因
Maybe that's why he wants his brother gone.

100
00:07:57,880 --> 00:07:59,960
安格 我要一杯祭奠酒
Ange, I need a libation.

101
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,640
我刚给过你一杯
I just poured you one.

102
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:06,920
我还能说什么呢? 我喜欢你的服务
Well, what can I say? I love the service.

103
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:09,160
天哪 迈卡
Jesus, Macca.

104
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:11,000
你认识山姆・卡拉汉吗?
Have you met Sam Callaghan?

105
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:15,960
没 但我听说过你 你是个调查员
No, but I've heard about you. You're the investigator.

106
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:19,440
安格・沃诺克 很高兴见到你
Ange Warnock. Pleased to meet you.

107
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:21,520
- 你好 - 我们得谈谈
- Yeah, g'day. - We have to talk.

108
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:23,160
我听说在中国城你有很多熟人
I hear you have contacts in Chinatown.

109
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:24,840
是吗? 谁告诉你的?
Yeah? Who told you that?

110
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:27,880
你随时可以来找我
You can always talk to me, you know.

111
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,120
瞧 谁来了
Mm. Look who's here.

112
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:35,480
你允许我加入了吗?
You going to fill me in?

113
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:37,600
毫无疑问
Absolutely.

114
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:42,120
想当记者
Wannabe journalist.

115
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:44,080
她很有才
She's good.

116
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:46,520
如果她老跟你聊 可成不了才
She won't be if she talks to you.

117
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:50,160
阿姆兰探长 对昨晚的枪击案有何看法?
Inspector Amran. Any comments on the shooting last night?

118
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:51,960
去和公共联络组谈吧
Go speak to the Public Liaison Unit.

119
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:53,960
你的朋友康在哪里?
Where's your friend Kang?

120
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:55,440
为什么问他? 他做了什么?
Why, what's he done?

121
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:58,080
他是我们昨晚击毙的恐怖分子的已知同谋
He's a known associate of the terrorist we shot last night.

122
00:08:58,240 --> 00:09:00,200
已知同谋? 嘿 那是啥意思?
A 'known associate'. Hey, what's that mean?

123
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:03,040
告诉你朋友 只要他能来自首
Tell your friend it will be safer for everyone

124
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:06,200
这样对大家都好
if he comes in on his own accord.

125
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:12,560
别太生气
Don't get too pissed.

126
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:15,280
当然不会
Of course not.

127
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:21,280
你昨晚被兰利的人盯上了
You got noticed last night at Langley.

128
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:24,000
我被打晕了就引起他们关注了?
Getting knocked out got me noticed?

129
00:09:24,160 --> 00:09:28,840
手无寸铁去抓恐怖分子 勇气可嘉 他们喜欢
Unarmed, chasing terrorists. Shows mettle. They like that.

130
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:33,120
炸弹袭击引起了他们的警戒
The bomb attack got their attention.

131
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:35,360
兰利的人想摸清楚新加坡每个人的底细
Langley wants a who's-who in the Singapore zoo

132
00:09:35,520 --> 00:09:38,200
跟齐基特合作的工会活动家
union activists who work with Chee Kit,

133
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:40,040
共产党拥护者 以及间谍
communist sympathisers, spies.

134
00:09:40,160 --> 00:09:41,880
你懂的
You know the drill.

135
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:44,920
所有不该拿到美国签证的人都需要调查
Pretty much anyone who shouldn't get a US visa.

136
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:46,880
看你的了
It's all yours.

137
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,640
这是什么?
What is this?

138
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:52,240
兰利的人说服军情六处跟我们共享情报
Langley convinced MI6 to share their intelligence with us.

139
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:54,440
米勒上校同意了?
And Major Miller agreed?

140
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:57,464
他跟我们一样担心共产主义分子啊 
He's as worried about the commies as we are. 

141
00:09:57,465 --> 00:09:58,360
玩得开心哦
Have fun.

142
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:22,240
三小时前你就该在这了
You were supposed to be here three hours ago.

143
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:25,080
- 警察在找你 - 所以呢?
- The cops are looking for you. - So?

144
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:27,080
阿姆兰说你认识昨晚被打死的那个人
Amran says you knew the guy they shot last night,

145
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:29,040
就是那个带炸弹的人
the guy with the bomb.

146
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:33,360
没错 他叫炎 在码头工作
Yeah. His name is Yam. He works on the wharfs.

147
00:10:33,520 --> 00:10:36,800
你也认识他 他不大爱讲话
You knew him too. He doesn't really talk to anybody.

148
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:40,640
- 你没帮工会跑过运输吧? - 没有
- You haven't done any transports for the unions, have you? - No.

149
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:42,920
- 康? - 我说了没有!
- Kang? - I said no!

150
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:45,120
他们已经在监视你了
They've got their eye on you.

151
00:10:45,280 --> 00:10:47,320
答应我别再做傻事了
Promise me you won't do anything stupid.

152
00:10:47,440 --> 00:10:49,600
好吧 随便啦
Yeah, whatever.

153
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:52,640
也许你也应该言而有信吧
Maybe you should start keeping your promises too.

154
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:54,192
这话什么意思? 
What's that supposed to mean?  

155
00:10:54,193 --> 00:10:55,760
别装蒜 你自己清楚
You know exactly what it means.

156
00:10:55,920 --> 00:10:58,520
你可以告诉辛普森太太 新加坡地方很小
And you can tell Mrs Simpson that Singapore is very small.

157
00:10:58,680 --> 00:11:01,960
你做了什么事 大家都看得见
When someone sees something, everybody sees it.

158
00:11:11,560 --> 00:11:13,751
我带着很多梦想来到这里 
I came here with such high hopes, 

159
00:11:13,752 --> 00:11:15,760
我不会错过任何一个的
but I won't miss any of this.

160
00:11:15,920 --> 00:11:18,120
你不会要去哪吧?
You're not going anywhere, are you?

161
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:19,880
不会
No.

162
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:21,880
别告诉我弗兰克被调走了
Oh, don't tell me Frank's been transferred?

163
00:11:22,040 --> 00:11:24,280
什么? 没 他没跟我说过
What? No, no, no. Not that he's told me.

164
00:11:27,640 --> 00:11:30,880
- 我记得你说过他周末才回来 - 没错
- I thought you said he was away till the weekend. - Mm. He is.

165
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,360
